From: Tuxbox Build System <build@tuxbox.org>
Date: Sun, 22 Dec 2024 18:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] gdbmopen: define blksize_t for uClibc

uClibc does not always define blksize_t in sys/types.h. Provide a
fallback definition if the type is not available.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [uClibc-specific]
Signed-off-by: Tuxbox Build System <build@tuxbox.org>

---
 src/gdbmopen.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/gdbmopen.c b/src/gdbmopen.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/src/gdbmopen.c
+++ b/src/gdbmopen.c
@@ -21,6 +21,11 @@
 #include "gdbmdefs.h"
 #include <stddef.h>

+/* uClibc may not define blksize_t */
+#ifndef _BLKSIZE_T_DEFINED
+typedef long blksize_t;
+#endif
+
 static void
 compute_directory_size (blksize_t block_size,
 			int *ret_dir_size, int *ret_dir_bits)
--
2.34.1
